<p><b>Is nuclear physics math?</b> The field is multidisciplinary, incorporating concepts in mathematics and physics, including those relating to thermodynamics, chemical reactions and the interactions between radiation and materials.</p>
<p><b>What is taught in nuclear physics?</b> Nuclear physics is the study of the structure of nuclei—their formation, stability, and decay. It aims to understand the fundamental nuclear forces in nature, their symmetries, and the resulting complex interactions between protons and neutrons in nuclei and among quarks inside hadrons, including the proton.</p>
