<p><b>What is the basic nuclear physics?</b> The nuclei of atoms are composed of protons, which have a positive electrical charge, and neutrons, which are electrically neutral. Electrons are electrically negative and have a charge equal in magnitude to that of a proton. The number of electrons in an atom is normally equal to the number of protons in the nucleus.</p>